Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Natasha Ng (nng752)

2023-03-08

My meme

This meme is a combination of my love for expensive Starbucks coffee and the Kombucha girl meme.

library(magick)

# first square
reaction_1 <- image_read("https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2019-08/13/23/asset/eb79be6c2790/sub-buzz-7759-1565737928-1.png?downsize=600:*&output-format=auto&output-quality=auto") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# second square
text_1 <- image_blank(width = 500,
                      height = 608,
                      color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "MAKING\n COFFEE AT\n HOME",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# third square
reaction_2 <- image_read("https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2019-08/13/23/asset/54a060f61328/sub-buzz-591-1565737963-1.png?downsize=600:*&output-format=auto&output-quality=auto") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# fourth square
text_2 <- image_blank(width = 500,
                      height = 608,
                      color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "BUYING\n COFFEE AT\n STARBUCKS",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# combining the four squares
top_row <- image_append(c(reaction_1, text_1))
bottom_row <- image_append(c(reaction_2, text_2))

meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)

# saving the meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

This animated GIF is basically how I felt this past 2 weeks learning R (from being absolutely confused to thinking ‘hey maybe it isn’t all that bad’)

library(magick)

frame_1 <- image_read("https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2019-08/13/23/asset/a5d3cf927328/sub-buzz-7878-1565737776-1.png?downsize=700%3A%2A&output-quality=auto&output-format=auto") %>%
  image_scale(1000) %>%
  image_extent("1000x1000")

frame_2 <- image_read("https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2019-08/13/23/asset/2b21cae68fe2/sub-buzz-1231-1565737889-1.png?downsize=700%3A%2A&output-quality=auto&output-format=auto") %>%
  image_scale(1000) %>%
  image_extent("1000x1000")

frame_3 <- image_read("https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2019-08/13/23/asset/eb79be6c2790/sub-buzz-7759-1565737928-1.png?downsize=600:*&output-format=auto&output-quality=auto") %>%
  image_scale(1000) %>%
  image_extent("1000x1000")

frame_4 <- image_read("https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2019-08/13/23/asset/54a060f61328/sub-buzz-591-1565737963-1.png?downsize=600:*&output-format=auto&output-quality=auto") %>%
  image_scale(1000) %>%
  image_extent("1000x1000")

# putting the frames in order using a vector
frames <- c(frame_1, frame_2, frame_3, frame_4)

# creating an animation
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Learning Stats220\n be like:", size = 100, , color = "#FFFFFF",gravity = "north")

# saving the animation
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
